        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 3:05AM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 305 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Melvern, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down twigs or small limbs and blow
around objects. Hail damage to outdoor objects and
vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pomona, Williamsburg, Quenemo, Melvern, and Pomona Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
